''This article is about the ''South Australia''n family of manufacturers. For the (unrelated) British legal historian and author'' '''Alfred William Brian Simpson''' ''see'' [[A. W. B. Simpson]].

'''Alfred Allen Simpson''' was [[List of Mayors and Lord Mayors of Adelaide|Mayor]] of the [[City of Adelaide]] from 1913 to 1915.

The name [[Simpson Desert]] was coined in 1930 by [[Cecil Madigan]],<ref>Madigan, C.T. 1930. An aerial reconnaissance into the southeastern portion of central Australia. Proceedings of the Royal Geographical Society of Australasia, South Australian Branch 30:83-108.</ref> after Alfred Allen Simpson, an Australian philanthropist, geographer, and president of the South Australian branch of the [[Royal Geographical Society of Australasia]].

From 1919, lived at [[Undelcarra]] in Burnside.<ref name=Undelcarra>[http://www.burnside.sa.gov.au/webdata/resources/files/unames.doc Undelcarra Road], Street names, City of Burnside</ref>

A. Simpson & Co., whitegoods manufacturer.<ref name=Undelcarra/>

